<p><b>Thermosiphon</b> (alt. <b>thermosyphon</b>) refers to a method of passive <a href="/wiki/Heat_exchange" title="Heat exchange">heat exchange</a> based on natural <a href="/wiki/Convection" title="Convection">convection</a> which circulates liquid in a vertical closed-loop circuit without requiring a conventional pump. Its intended purpose is to simplify the pumping of liquid and/or heat transfer, by avoiding the cost and complexity of a conventional liquid pump.</p>
